Date: Thu, 5 Feb 2004 22:49:44 -0200
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinhuaNet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-02/05/content_1299984.htm>

Unknown disease makes 90 Nepalese people ill
--------------------------------------------
At least 90 persons have taken seriously ill with an unknown disease which
has spread in the past few days in Nepal's central district of Dolakha, The
Rising Nepal newspaper reported Thu, 4 Feb 2004.
The symptoms of the disease are breathing difficulty, fever, giddiness,
lethargy, and cough, the state-run English daily quoted Dinesh Upreti,
chairman of Pawati village in the district, as saying.
Those infected range in age from 1.5 to 75 years, and most of them came
from Pawati village, more than 100 km northeast of Kathmandu, Upreti said.
A 3-member medical team has been sent to the village to treat the patients,
he added.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The etiology of this febrile illness associated with cough and shortness
of breath is not known at this point. More epidemiological information and
clinical data are needed. The number of cases seems quite excessive if
this is avian influenza. - Mod.LL]
